\begin_layout Standard
While the unrestricted method provided by McKelvey does allow us to explain
 differences in quality in consumer choice, it is not sufficient to demonstrate
 the substitution between assets purchased and quality demanded.
 As explained before, since we wish to understand conspicuous consumption
 with an intertemporal substitution approach, the modeling of uncertainty
