 where the household is located.
 It is worth clarifying that we make no attempts to arrive at a price granularit
y lower than that of a district.
 Whenever there are multiple price observations at the district level, we
 arrive a district-level price using a regression (discussed below).
 For items such as electricity and gas which are limited to a few urban
